            . I am a <rs id="t18191201-154-viclabel882" type="occupation">bookbinder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191201-154-victim1537 t18191201-154-viclabel882"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18191201-154-crimeloc883">Charter House-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18191201-154-crimeloc883" type="placeName" value="Charter House-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18191201-154-crimeloc883" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191201-154-off880 t18191201-154-crimeloc883"></join>. On the 30th of November, about eleven o'clock, the prisoner came from his master for some books; they were not done, and he waited for them till about one o'clock. During that time I left him alone, and about two hours after he was gone I missed these tools. I went and charged him with it - he denied it, but at last gave me the duplicate.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-154-person1539">
                  JOHN 
                  DENSEA
               <interp inst="t18191201-154-person1539" type="surname" value="DENSEA"></interp>
